#- 

         +-+-+-+   ☆ 
    ♫  ~|  THE  |~      
        +-+-+-+-+
     ~| BALLAD OF |~
     +-+-+-+-+-+-+    
  ☆   ~| MAYBLU |~  ♬
     +-+-+-+-+-+-+
    ~| THE MIGHTY |~
      +-+-+-+-+-+
#-  +∋*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*∈+




        MALAFLY'S
 ◎ HERO COMPENDIUM ◎

          BOOK I




 +∋*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*∈+
#- 
    You may find, in          modern times, a     
        rampant
    self-obsession.

 Where kindness is not    given without the      pairing of a question. 
   Where goodness wears a gilded mask to beg its own reflection.
#- 
  Yet still the sun will      feed the field, the     beggar, and the king.

  It does not ask the    hearts it warms what   gratitude they bring.

    To give is in its     nature, as the song is     to the string.
#-     Now greed has         clouded hearts and    deeds, and rainfall      feeds the stone.

 The streetlamps, too,   are desperate for a   warmth they've never           known.

 For those that shine   yet loathe their light    make cold the love        they've shown.
#-     
     Mayblu arose       beneath the weight of  all the world's disdain.

 Her spirit pressed by    ceaseless care,      became a diamond vein.

 And from that buried  hurt was born a hope     that shall remain.
#-   Some give for show,   some give for shame,    their hearts both        bound and blind.

  They wait for coin,     for praise, for proof  of what they've left            behind.

  The lagging streets  are choked with greed  while Mayblu gives in              kind.
#- 
The search for those  to give to is itself a          joyful art.

  Each gift bestowed     with understanding     nourishes the heart.

    The giver and          receiver share a      single, sacred part.
#- 
 You often say "I give    to those who have      deserved my hand",

 But the river flows to all of those who thirst      upon the land.

     The courage to        accept the gift is          strength few              understand.
#- 
    Do not wait for        asking, do not seek      reward or fame.

  The open-handed     giver knew her worth      is not in name.

   Her life became a     river flowing steady         without claim.


#- 




  Upon those shifting     banks we thank that    Mayblu's in our game.

#- 